Paper: hep-th/9810250

Date: 1998-10-30

Title: 3-Sasakian Manifolds

Authors: Charles P. Boyer and Krzysztof Galicki

Comments: 59 pages, to appear in Essays on Einstein Manifolds, M. Wang and C.

LeBrun, edsJournal-ref: Surveys Diff.Geom. 7 (1999) 123-184

This is an expository paper describing the geometry of certainSasakian-Einstein manifolds. Such manifolds have recently become of interestdue to Maldacena's AdS/CFT conjecture. They describe near-horizon geometries ofbranes at conical singularities.